  "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Problem\r\nThe onboarding flow has recently been updated. Part of the onboarding flow includes a screen `Select key storage` asking the user to select where they want to store their newly generated key.\r\n\r\nThis screen includes the options to select:\r\n\r\nDefault\r\n\r\n- This device\r\n\r\nAdvanced\r\n\r\n- Keycard\r\n\r\nPurpose of this screen is a) functional (select storage location) and b) non-functional (communicate that the keys are stored locally, no servers, no backup).\r\n\r\nThis screen is currently not shown on iOS, presumably as `This device` is the only option as Keycard hasn't been implemented for iOS yet. Given it's non-functional/communication purpose use we'd like to see it included in Onboarding for iOS with only the default option visible.\r\n\r\n![Key storage1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35233054/67584358-b869e180-f74d-11e9-8bb2-066fe05cd4fe.png)\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\nPlease ping @errorists and/or @hesterbruikman for review\r\n\r\n## Future Steps\r\n\r\n",
